detective /dɪˈtɛktɪv/

(detectives) 

1. N-COUNT A detective is someone whose job is to discover what has happened in a crime or other situation and to find the people involved. Some detectives work in the police force and others work privately. 侦探 

例： Now detectives are appealing for witnesses who may have seen anything suspicious last night. 现在侦探们正在呼吁昨晚可能看到任何可疑情况的人出来作证。 

2. ADJ A detective novel or story is one in which a detective tries to solve a crime. 侦探的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...Arthur Conan Doyle's classic detective novel. …阿瑟·柯南·道尔的经典侦探小说。

